result.execSummary:
The defendant Lori J Luckey was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

Defendant Lori J Luckey in court, in custody, with attorney Adam J. Schleis.   Jayne Davis Dewire appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea to count #1. Court performs plea colloquy and finds defendant guilty of count #1. State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Schleis makes statements regarding sentencing. Defendant makes Statements. Defendant sentenced to the following:

COUNT#1:

JAIL: 7 DAYS (7 days credit for time served)

COSTS:  $243.00 + $200.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid at $25/month commencing on 01/04/16)

Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided,   immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

Defendant to have no contact with Michael F. listed in the Criminal Complaint or his residence.  Defendant not to possess any identifying information other than herself.  Provide current correct address.
Waukesha County Pretrial Screening Services Report by Wisconsin Community Services filed.

Defendant Lori J Luckey in court, in custody.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Adam Schleis appears as friend of the court.  Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  An attorney will be appointed.  Defendant allowed free phone calls to obtain bail.  Hearing scheduled for December 1, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
